Initial Jobless Claims
   Declined to 437,000
   In Week Ended Feb. 22
In the week ended Feb. 15, 3,259,000 people were receiving
state unemployment benefits, down 55,000 from the previous
week's revised level. The number of people receiving
unemployment benefits as a percentage of those covered by
unemployment insurance was unchanged at 3.1%.
   Counting all state and federal programs, the number of
people receiving unemployment benefits in the week ended Feb.
15 fell to 4,085,008 from 4,147,555 the prior week. These
figures aren't seasonally adjusted.
   This morning, the Labor Department will issues its report
on employment and unemployment for February, the government's
first broad look at the economy during the month.